<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1163,2054]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,488,1163,1189]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Habitat and distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="emend. Ruiz-Sanchez, Mejia-Saules, Cortes &amp; L. G. Clark" authorityYear="2014" box="[523,769,1163,1189]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="enigmatica">
<emphasis box="[523,769,1163,1189]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Chusquea enigmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a single locality in 
<collectingRegion box="[1237,1397,1163,1189]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Veracruz state</collectingRegion>
in a montane cloud forest dominated by 
<taxonomicName box="[559,769,1199,1225]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Fagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis box="[559,769,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Fagus grandiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lundell" authorityYear="1937" box="[831,1074,1199,1225]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapotaceae" genus="Podocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="matudae">
<emphasis box="[831,1074,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Podocarpus matudae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at 
<quantity box="[1116,1205,1199,1225]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.96" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" unit="m" value="1960.0">1960 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ruiz-Sanchez, E. &amp; Mejia-Saules, M. T. &amp; Clark, L. G." pageId="3" pageNumber="50" pagination="16 - 26" refId="ref7242" refString="Ruiz-Sanchez, E., Mejia-Saules, M. T. &amp; Clark, L. G. (2014 a) A new endangered species of Chusquea (Poaceae: Bambusoideae) from the Acatlain volcano in central Veracruz, Mexico, and keys to the Mexican Chusquea species. Phytotaxa 163: 16 - 26." type="journal article" year="2014">
Ruiz-Sanchez 
<emphasis box="[1391,1452,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2014a
</bibRefCitation>
). However, new collections were made from 
<collectingRegion box="[721,1044,1235,1261]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Hidalgo and San Luis Potosí</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[1060,1140,1235,1261]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1022,1044]" captionTargetBox="[175,1411,202,986]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[164,1423,190,998]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Geographical distribution map of Chusquea enigmatica and C. septentrionalis. Black squares belong to C. enigmatica, black triangles are localities of C. septentrionalis. Black arrows indicate the type locality for each species. Dotted line indicates previous northernmost Chusquea collections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809780" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809780/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1153,1167,1235,1261]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[193,1404,214,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-28@4.[170,1416,190,1751]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chusquea enigmatica. A. Plants of C. enigmatica in the understory of the montane cloud forest in the State of San Luis Potosí, Mexico. B. Plants of C. enigmatica growing in a clearing of the montane cloud forest in the State of Hidalgo, Mexico. C. Leptmorph rhizome. D-E. Branches and foliage leaves from Hidalgo (D) and San Luis Potosí (E). A, E. Photos by Julián Hernández Rendón. B-D. Photos by Eduardo Ruiz-Sanchez." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809782" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809782/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">3</figureCitation>
) in montane cloud forest at elevations of 
<quantity box="[314,472,1271,1298]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8765" metricValueMax="2.0149999999999997" metricValueMin="1.738" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" unit="m" value="1876.5" valueMax="2015.0" valueMin="1738.0">1738–2015 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1163,2054]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,337,1307,1333]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Comparison</emphasis>
:—Synflorescences and spikelets of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="emend. Ruiz-Sanchez, Mejia-Saules, Cortes &amp; L. G. Clark" authorityYear="2014" box="[763,1010,1307,1333]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="enigmatica">
<emphasis box="[763,1010,1307,1333]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Chusquea enigmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1296,1451,1307,1333]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[1296,1451,1307,1333]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">C. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[143,231,1343,1369]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[136,224,159,183]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of reproductive characters between Chusquea enigmatica and C. lanceolata." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF3FBDF6FFFDFFF1FF6BFF4199C3FF6C" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" tableUuid="DF3FBDF6FFFDFFF1FF6BFF4199C3FF6C">Table 1</tableCitation>
). However, although the primary synflorescence branches in both species are spreading, all higher-order branchlets and pedicels in 
<taxonomicName box="[439,591,1379,1405]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[439,458,1379,1405]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[473,591,1379,1405]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are appressed to the primary branches, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="emend. Ruiz-Sanchez, Mejia-Saules, Cortes &amp; L. G. Clark" authorityYear="2014" box="[1177,1335,1379,1405]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="enigmatica">
<emphasis box="[1177,1196,1379,1405]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1211,1335,1380,1405]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">enigmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, these are also spreading. The sizes of glumes I, II, III and IV are somewhat larger in 
<taxonomicName box="[978,1129,1415,1441]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[978,997,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1011,1129,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the abaxial indument is different. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="emend. Ruiz-Sanchez, Mejia-Saules, Cortes &amp; L. G. Clark" authorityYear="2014" box="[247,492,1451,1477]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="enigmatica">
<emphasis box="[247,492,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Chusquea enigmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has scabrous and awned glumes III and IV, and these are pubescent below the apex and subulate in 
<taxonomicName box="[313,464,1487,1513]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[313,464,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">C. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Glume IV is 1-nerved in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="emend. Ruiz-Sanchez, Mejia-Saules, Cortes &amp; L. G. Clark" authorityYear="2014" box="[759,916,1487,1513]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="enigmatica">
<emphasis box="[759,916,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">C. enigmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 3-, 5- or 7-nerved in 
<taxonomicName box="[1204,1355,1487,1513]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[1204,1355,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">C. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the lemma is 5-nerved in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="emend. Ruiz-Sanchez, Mejia-Saules, Cortes &amp; L. G. Clark" authorityYear="2014" box="[380,537,1523,1549]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="enigmatica">
<emphasis box="[380,537,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">C. enigmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 7- or 9-nerved in 
<taxonomicName box="[788,938,1523,1549]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[788,938,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">C. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[953,1037,1523,1549]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[136,224,159,183]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of reproductive characters between Chusquea enigmatica and C. lanceolata." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF3FBDF6FFFDFFF1FF6BFF4199C3FF6C" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" tableUuid="DF3FBDF6FFFDFFF1FF6BFF4199C3FF6C">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1163,2054]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1559,1585]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The specific epithet refers to the unusual morphology with leptomorph rhizomes and reduction in bud and culm sizes and the consequent difficulty in classifying this species within one of the known sections of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1822" box="[136,248,1631,1657]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,248,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Chusquea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1163,2054]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,313,1667,1693]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Phenology</emphasis>
:— The first known flowering record for this species occurred during the summer of 2019 (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">S. Zamudio, J. Ceja &amp; A. Mendoza 17454</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
